=3D"anchored-header__link" data-clipboard-text=3D"https://developer.masterc=
ard.com/product/mastercard-account-validation/#benefits"></a>Benefits</h2><=
hr class=3D"light"></div>
<div class=3D"grid">
<div class=3D"grid-item">
  <div class=3D"grid-item-content"><p><img src=3D"https://static.developer.=
mastercard.com/content/account-validation/uploads/additional_fraud_deterren=
t.svg" alt=3D"Additional fraud deterrent"></p>
<div class=3D"anchored-header"><h5 id=3D"additional-fraud-checks">Additiona=
l fraud checks</h5><hr class=3D"light"></div>
<p>Protect against fraudulent card use and account takeover by checking the=
 supplied name matches the name associated with the card at the issuer</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"grid-item">
  <div class=3D"grid-item-content"><p><img src=3D"https://static.developer.=
mastercard.com/content/account-validation/uploads/real_time_verification.sv=
g" alt=3D"Real-time verification"></p>
<div class=3D"anchored-header"><h5 id=3D"real-time-validation">Real-time va=
lidation</h5><hr class=3D"light"></div>
<p>Reduce customer friction by validating card accounts quickly with card i=
ssuers* via the trusted Mastercard Network and getting simple name match re=
sults</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"grid-item">
  <div class=3D"grid-item-content"><p><img src=3D"https://static.developer.=
mastercard.com/content/account-validation/uploads/efficiency.svg" alt=3D"Si=
mple integration"></p>
<div class=3D"anchored-header"><h5 id=3D"simple-secure-integration">Simple =
secure integration</h5><hr class=3D"light"></div>
<p>Provides a single secure API connection to major card networks, with opt=
ional payload encryption</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>* Exceptions occur when the Receive Network has not enabled issuer v=
erification of account/name information or the issuer cannot or does not pr=
ovide a response. Mastercard can provide on-behalf results for Mastercard i=
ssuers where configured.</em></p>
<hr>
<div class=3D"anchored-header"><h2 id=3D"how-it-works"><a title=3D"" class=
=3D"anchored-header__link" data-clipboard-text=3D"https://developer.masterc=
ard.com/product/mastercard-account-validation/#how-it-works"></a>How it wor=
ks</h2><hr class=3D"light"></div>
<p>The <strong>Mastercard Account Validation</strong> API service enables M=
astercard customers to validate that the name of a registered cardholder ma=
tches the name(s) associated with the account held by the card issuer. The =
service can also validate the Card Verification Code (CVC or CVV).</p>
<p>Establishing account ownership is a critical step in protecting payments=
 and funds transfers. Fraud is growing and becoming more sophisticated, esp=
ecially across unauthorized account takeover and authorized push payment sc=
ams. Regulatory bodies are recognizing the fraud risks and are introducing =
new account validation requirements. This API service helps establish accou=
nt ownership and detect fraud before it occurs, for example, during initial=
 account opening, card registration or periodically in advance of collectin=
g or crediting funds.</p>
<p>Example online marketplace app:</p>
<div class=3D"grid">
<div class=3D"grid-item">
  <div class=3D"grid-item-content"><p><img src=3D"https://static.developer.=
mastercard.com/content/account-validation/product/img/hiw-01-account-info.p=
ng" alt=3D"Example use - user adds new card details">
In the marketplace app, Jill adds details of a new card account to transfer=
 funds from or to that card</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"grid-item">
  <div class=3D"grid-item-content"><p><img src=3D"https://static.developer.=
mastercard.com/content/account-validation/product/img/hiw-02.png" alt=3D"Ex=
ample use - API request">
You, the app provider, check the card account by sending the supplied name =
and account details in an Account Validation API call</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"grid-item">
  <div class=3D"grid-item-content"><p><img src=3D"https://static.developer.=
mastercard.com/content/account-validation/product/img/hiw-03-avs.png" alt=
=3D"Example use - network message to card issuer">
Mastercard validates the supplied details with the card issuer using an Acc=
ount Name Inquiry request</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"grid-item">
  <div class=3D"grid-item-content"><p><img src=3D"https://static.developer.=
mastercard.com/content/account-validation/product/img/hiw-03-oi-av.png" alt=
=3D"Example use - API response with matching values">
Mastercard returns a matching response to you, which helps you determine ac=
count validity and whether to allow Jill to proceed with the transfer</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> Effective 3 June 2025, issuers in the Canada and =
United States regions are required to support cardholder name validation fu=
nctionality by responding to Name Validation Service (NVS) request messages=
. The service supports Mastercard debit, credit, and prepaid card accounts.=
 In the U.S., the service also supports Visa debit; Mastercard Send will ro=
ute the query to the appropriate Network.</p>
<hr>
